    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-26T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1136</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d84fn1">The same, on the same date, to the
                        Ambassador in France (No. 3229).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-26T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6683. Please inform the Foreign Office orally that the Department is in receipt
                    of a telegram from Vladivostok from a reliable American army officer who has
                    spent some time traveling in eastern Siberia investigating conditions there. He
                    reports that the Russian population would be most decidedly unfriendly to the
                    entry of Japanese troops unless accompanied by other Allied forces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
